Note:
Runa Standard Library: Blockchain Compliance Rules Module

Provides comprehensive regulatory compliance framework for blockchain systems and
decentralized applications. Implements enterprise-grade compliance mechanisms including
KYC/AML procedures, regulatory reporting, sanctions screening, and jurisdiction-specific
rules. Competitive with production compliance implementations in regulated financial
institutions and compliant DeFi protocols.

Features:
- Know Your Customer (KYC) and Anti-Money Laundering (AML) procedures
- Sanctions screening against global watchlists (OFAC, UN, EU)
- Transaction monitoring and suspicious activity detection
- Regulatory reporting and audit trail generation
- Jurisdiction-specific compliance rules and frameworks
- Privacy-preserving compliance with zero-knowledge proofs
- Real-time risk scoring and transaction blocking
- Compliance officer tools and administrative interfaces
- Cross-border transaction compliance and reporting
- Tax calculation and withholding for different jurisdictions
- Data protection and privacy regulation compliance (GDPR, CCPA)
- Securities law compliance for tokenized assets
- Banking regulation compliance (Basel III, MiFID II)
- Insurance and reinsurance regulatory frameworks
- Environmental and sustainability compliance reporting
:End Note

Note: Core Compliance Types
